end, leadership vs the index/sector, and tradeability.","why_it_can_fail":"corporate-action gaps, illiquid names, or a short listing history can distort returns/DMA/RS."}},"business":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"flags":[{"label":"Business quality","value":58.5,"unit":"/100","status":"ok","read":"Average quality (58/100).","meaning":"Composite of profitability, return on capital, balance-sheet safety and cash conversion (the Fundamentals-tab Quality score).","why_useful":"A durable, high-return business compounds value; a low-quality one needs a bigger margin of safety.","why_it_can_fail":"A single composite can mask a weak component; open the Fundamentals tab for the breakdown."},{"label":"Cash conversion","value":4.6,"unit":"\u00d7","status":"good","read":"4.60\u00d7 of profit came in as operating cash (5-yr median) \u2014 well backed.","meaning":"Median of (cash from operations \u00f7 net profit) over the last 5 years.","why_useful":"Profit you can't collect as cash is fragile; >0.8\u00d7 means earnings are real cash, <0.6\u00d7 is an accrual red flag.","why_it_can_fail":"One-off working-capital swings or a capex year can distort a single ratio; the 5-yr median smooths it."},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":0.49,"unit":"\u00d7 D/E","status":"weak","read":"Leveraged (D/E 0.49\u00d7, interest cover 1.1\u00d7).","meaning":"Latest debt-to-equity and interest coverage (EBIT \u00f7 interest) from the balance sheet.","why_useful":"Low debt and high interest cover let a business survive a downturn; high debt amplifies trouble.","why_it_can_fail":"Off-balance-sheet leases/guarantees aren't captured; a cash-rich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":31.25,"unit":"% YoY","status":"ok","read":"Profit up 31% YoY \u2014 modest.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":95.6,"pe_percentile":7.0,"median_pe":150.1,"earnings_yield_pct":1.05,"pb":3.13,"ev_ebitda":29.74,"quality_score":58.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":null,"peg":null,"cheapness":{"status":"good","read":"P/E at the 7-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 cheap vs its own history."},"expectations":"Trades at 95.6\u00d7 earnings; multi-year growth not estimable, so 'priced-in' growth is unclear.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[62.85,62.85,62.75,62.72,62.61,62.59,62.57,62.57,62.55,62.53,62.53],"latest_pct":62.53,"chg_1y_pp":-0.04},"FII":{"periods":["Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[10.51,10.46,0.51,0.29,0.5,0.28,0.31,0.32,0.67,0.4,0.5],"latest_pct":0.5,"chg_1y_pp":0.19},"DII":{"periods":["Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[11.98,12.03,8.07,7.83,8.29,9.54,9.6,10.3,8.66,9.06,9.58],"latest_pct":9.58,"chg_1y_pp":-0